review_blob: Pours smooth, little head, dark carmel color and a sweet smell of honey and vanilla. Taste the barrel age well. Hints of bourbon and smoke. Great flavor.
beer_name: New Glory Honey Springs Bourbon Ale

review_blob: Heavy aroma of mosaic. Great mouth feel. A little bitter off the back end but delicious none the less. Great beer
For the style I thought this beer was a little malty. Nose was mostly from the malt. The Citra doesnt come across like I am used to. Not my favorite but decent.
beer_name: Against the Grain Citra Ass Down

review_blob: Mosaic hop forward beer. Great clean clips mouth. Easy drinking beer. Light in color. Easy bite on the front with a clean finish.
Great aroma right off the bat! Crisp mouth feel with a nice after taste of citrus. First 10 barrel beer for me and I like it!
